          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The softmax filter is applied across feature channels in a convolutional manner at all spatial locations. The softmax filter can be seen as the combination of an activation function (exponential) and a normalization operator.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "For each feature channel per pixel in an image in a feature map, the softmax filter computes the following:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "identifier": "media-2903559",
              "metadata": {
                "anchor": "2903559",
                "title": "Figure 1"
              },
              "type": "image"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Where ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "R",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " is the result channel in the pixel and ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "N",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " is the number of feature channels.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
